    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Start the salsa verde</strong></p> <p>Boil a kettle.</p> <p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong> and <strong>basil</strong> finely (including the stalks).</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/british-hake-butter-bean-puree-heritage-tomatoes-and-salsa-verde/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Add the remaining ingredients</strong>\u00a0</p> <p>Add the <strong>pine nuts</strong>, <strong>capers</strong> and <strong>sultanas</strong> to the <strong>chopped herbs</strong> and chop everything together as finely as you can.</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/british-hake-butter-bean-puree-heritage-tomatoes-and-salsa-verde/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Finish the salsa verde</strong></p> <p>Add the mix to a bowl with the juice of 1/4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1/2]</span> <strong>lemon</strong> and 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong>.</p> <p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>salsa verde</strong>.</p> <p>\u00a0</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/british-hake-butter-bean-puree-heritage-tomatoes-and-salsa-verde/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Start the butter bean pur\u00e9e</strong></p> <p>Dissolve 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1]</span>\u00a0<strong>Knorr</strong>\u00a0<strong>vegetable stock cube</strong> in 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>.</p> <p>Peel and chop the <strong>garlic</strong> roughly.</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/british-hake-butter-bean-puree-heritage-tomatoes-and-salsa-verde/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Finish the butter bean\u00a0pur\u00e9e</strong></p> <p>Drain and rinse the <strong>butter beans</strong> and add them to a <strong>food processor</strong>.</p> <p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (don't like raw garlic? Go easy!) with the juice of 1/4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1/2]</span> <strong>lemon</strong>,\u00a0<strong>vegetable stock</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>.</p> <p>Blitz until smooth \u2013 this is your<strong> butter bean pure\u00e9</strong>.</p> <p>Tip: If you don't have a food processor, you can mash the beans instead.</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/british-hake-butter-bean-puree-heritage-tomatoes-and-salsa-verde/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Cook your fish </strong></p> <p>Pat the\u00a0<strong>hake</strong>\u00a0dry with kitchen towel. Season with a pinch of\u00a0<strong>salt</strong>.</p> <p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of\u00a0<strong>vegetable oil</strong>\u00a0over a high heat. Once very hot, add the\u00a0<strong>hake</strong>, skin-side down, and cook for 4-5 minutes or until the skin has started to crisp.</p> <p>Flip the\u00a0fish\u00a0and cook for 1-2 minutes further or until cooked through. Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily.</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/british-hake-butter-bean-puree-heritage-tomatoes-and-salsa-verde/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Prepare your heritage tomatoes</strong></p> <p>Slice the\u00a0<strong>heritage tomatoes</strong>\u00a0in half.</p> <p>Season with a generous pinch of\u00a0<strong>salt</strong>.</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/british-hake-butter-bean-puree-heritage-tomatoes-and-salsa-verde/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Serve up!</strong></p> <p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lemon</strong> into wedges.</p> <p>Serve the <strong>pan-fried hake</strong> over the <strong>butter bean pure\u00e9</strong> with the <strong>heritage tomatoes</strong> to the side.</p> <p>Drizzle the<strong> salsa verde</strong> over and garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong>.</p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
